.PP
Determines the default parameters that this socket tries to negotiate with its peer while establishing an association with it. Is to be set after \fIopen/*\fR but before the first \fIconnect/*\fR. \fI#sctp_initmsg{}\fR can also be used as ancillary data with the first call of \fIsend/*\fR to a new peer (when a new association is created).

num_ostreams
.RS 2
Number of outbound streams


.RE

max_instreams
.RS 2
Maximum number of inbound streams


.RE

max_attempts
.RS 2
Maximum retransmissions while establishing an association


.RE

max_init_timeo
.RS 2
Time-out, in milliseconds, for establishing an association


.RE

.RE

{sctp_autoclose, integer() >= 0}
.RS 2
Determines the time, in seconds, after which an idle association is automatically closed. 
\fI0\fR means that the association is never automatically closed.

.RE

{sctp_nodelay, true|false}
.RS 2
Turns off (
\fItrue\fR) / on (\fIfalse\fR) the Nagle algorithm for merging small packets into larger ones. This improves throughput at the expense of latency.

.RE

{sctp_disable_fragments, true|false}
.RS 2
If 
\fItrue\fR, induces an error on an attempt to send a message larger than the current PMTU size (which would require fragmentation/reassembling). Notice that message fragmentation does not affect the logical atomicity of its delivery; this option is provided for performance reasons only.

.RE

{sctp_i_want_mapped_v4_addr, true|false}
.RS 2
Turns on|off automatic mapping of IPv4 addresses into IPv6 ones (if the socket address family is 
\fIAF_INET6\fR).

.RE

{sctp_maxseg, integer()}
.RS 2
Determines the maximum chunk size if message fragmentation is used. If 
\fI0\fR, the chunk size is limited by the Path MTU only.

.RE


